events.name: Join GDG Ramallah
events.description:
GDG Ramallah is a Palestinian chapter of the global Google Developer Groups (GDGs).
The group was started by a group of Google fans and enthusiasts who are interested in using Google's devolving technologies.
Google Developer Groups (GDGs) are for developers who are interested in Google's developer technology; everything from the Android, Chrome, Drive, and Google Cloud platforms, to product APIs like the Cast API, Maps API, and YouTube API.

Membership in this group is open to beginners, developers and Google lovers. Also all people interested in technology, and in particular Google technology are most welcome to join us not just developers.
We take Ramallah City and want to make Birzeit University as center of our operation. Therefore, we need to expand our team by join new Co-organizers from Computer Engineering students of Birzeit University.
So, we welcome you to join GDG Ramallah as a members or Co-organizers by filling the following form.
Membership and volunteering is open to all, but for organizers we will choose two from Birzeit university students depending on the following application form. https://goo.gl/forms/OE7HRZhojTUaLR9l2

events.name: Google Mobile Web Certification StudyJam
events.description:
• What we'll do
Want to sharpen your mobile web skills? Join our study jam to get mobile site certified!
30/1/2018 - 3/2/2018

GDG Ramallah is organizing a study jam on mobile site certification.
The Mobile Sites certification is a professional accreditation that Google offers to individuals who demonstrate proficiency in basic and advanced aspects of mobile website design and development. A Mobile Sites certification allows individuals to demonstrate that Google recognizes them as an expert in mobile sites.

This is a chance to get a professional accreditation that demonstrates you have an understanding of basic and advanced aspects of mobile website design and development. By learning together we think it’s going to be more fun and more of us are going to be able to complete it.

Benefits include:

• Certificate: Show that you're a certified mobile sites professional with a personalized certificate that you can print!

• Profile page: Share your expertise with a Google Partners public profile page that lists your certifications.

This meetup will explain the benefits of getting certified, how to get certified, and how to share and communicate your certification status with others.

• What to bring
Laptop , Notebooks and Pens

• Important to know

#MobileSiteCertification #Google

events.name: Google Cloud Study Jam
events.description:
• What we'll do
What is a Study Jam?
Study Jams are community-run study groups for students on Google Developers content, on various product topics.
The objective of Study Jams is to raise the technical proficiency of our community members through the highest possible course completion rate.

What is Cloud Study Jam?
Learn the fundamentals of the Google Cloud Platform, how to run containers on it and how to use the platform for data engineering. Attendees get free access to the labs ($70+ value). No need to create a Google Cloud Platform account or register with a credit card.

How long does it take?
One in-person session of 3 hours, followed by 2-8 hours of self-study.

What is the end result?
Google-hosted badges that attendees can use in their online profiles and show to employers.

events.name: Actions on Google Assistant
events.description:
“Build Actions for Your Community”

What we'll do
"Build Actions for Your Community" is a 1-day event for developers of all skill level to come together to learn how to create Actions for Google Assistant. The event features a blend of tech talks, code labs, discussions, demos and networking.

The Google Assistant is the conversational user interface that helps user's get things done in their world. Actions on Google lets developers extend the Assistant to implement their own Conversation Actions. This talk will explain everything you need to know about designing a conversation and persona, and implementing it using the Actions SDK and API.AI (http://api.ai/) tools.

*Lunch, coffee/snacks, wifi are provided.
*Lucky draw with grand prize.

events.description:
It's time to Google I/O Extended
Let us celebrate the yearly tradition of Google announcements.

GDG Ramallah will host a Google I/O Extended where you can join us for a screening and watch the live stream from the keynote in San Francisco and discuss this year's announcements and highlights from Google.

I/O brings together developers from around the globe for talks, hands-on learning with Google experts, and a first look at Google’s latest developer products.

After I/O Keynote Streaming, GDG Ramallah presents you one of the biggest events of the year by extending Google I/O 2018!

This year, I/O Extended event brings you code labs on an exquisite new technology revolutionizing the way things are done in Android Mobiles. I/O Extended event will also focus on sessions about Flutter.

What is Flutter?

Flutter is a mobile app SDK for building high-performance, high-fidelity, apps for iOS and Android, from a single codebase.

events.name: Google Hash Code 2019
events.description:
Google Hash Code is back! You've had a year to sharpen up your coding skills and now is the time to put them to the test. Are you up for the challenge?

Hash Code is a team-based programming competition for university students and industry professionals across Europe, Middle East, and Africa (EMEA). Teams will be tasked with solving algorithmic problems that are inspired by real challenges that people face at Google. In March there'll be an Online Qualification Round, and the top scoring teams from this round will then be invited to the Google Dublin office to compete in the final round of the competition in April.

The competition is divided into two stages:

• Online Qualification Round on 28 February
• Final Round (at an international Google office) on 27 April

For the Online Qualification Round, we're encouraging you to join us at the GDG London hub to compete side-by-side in a more fun environment.

Registration to compete in Google Hash Code 2019 is MANDATORY! Follow the steps:
1. Sign up here — https://codingcompetitions.withgoogle.com/hashcode
2. Create a new team or join one of the existing teams using the invitation link.
3. Select the GDG Ramallah hub
